Harrison shot our engagement session last month and we couldn't be happier with our photos. He has a keen eye for the photojournalistic style we were looking for, which was a top priority in my search for a photographer. The shoot was fun, relaxed, and natural. We brought our dog for the first half of the shoot and Harrison even captured some amazing, frame-worthy portraits of her by herself. She quietly stole our show!  Price-wise, Harrison fit right into our budget. I was looking for a photographer that was willing to give us the digital files of our photos. He charges an additional fee for this, but the total cost was still less than what I would have paid other photographers for just the engagement shoot. One photographer quoted me more than double for the same package, so Harrison's pricing was very fair, in my opinion.   We are planning on having another photographer shoot our wedding overseas, but had we arranged for a local wedding, I would have loved Harrison to shoot for us again. When the time comes, I will be knocking on Harrison's door again for family portraits!

