I went to Tortoise & Hare Sports on Friday night to pick up my team's race packets for Saturday's Color Me Rad run. I live in Central Phoenix, so this location is faaaaar for me, but after a friendly neighbor recommended it, I was happy to make the trek up to Glendale and check the place out. Plus, I was in need of new running shoes - how convenient!   My experience at Tortoise & Hare Sports was fantastic. Nathan, the owner, found me a great pair of shoes and inserts after evaluating my feet and my natural foot strike. He whipped out his handy iPad and recorded my foot strike running away and towards back him while outside, determining that the shoes were a good fit, preventing any pronation that I would otherwise have.    I have to say Nathan got it right with his knowledge, experience, and top notch customer service. He was kind throughout the process and I never felt any pressure to spend. The only drawback for me was the distance. Maybe he'll be open to expanding into Central Phoenix in the near future... ;)

